        public java.lang.Class<?> findClass​(java.net.URL url,
                                    java.lang.String name)
                             throws java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        Searches a URL representing a jar file for the specified class.
        Parameters:
        url - the URL of the jar file to search
        name - the class name
        Returns:
        the found class, or null if not found
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - only if there was an underlying error accessing the temporary file to be searched
